<br>
Vorphuix found his spells in Erudin but still haven't heard of the bad news of his wife's death. He left Erudin and came back to Qeynos when he was told of what happened. He traveled back to freeport and got onto the boat. He didn't know it would be his last ride. It was a stormy ride across the ocean. The boat came to a dock and was attacked by Seafury Cyclop's. His Corpse was never found.<br>
<br>
The Wizard Guild tryed to explain all this to a young boy, and wanted him to follow in his fathers footsteps of becoming a great Wizard. Asphyx left quite angry and didn't listen. He went straight to the general and told them to revenge his mother's and father's death, But the General was too busy to help, Felwithe, and Ak'non found another island and had to many troops away to take over Mistmoore Castle. But the General gave Asphyx a suit of full bronze armor and a claymore. Asphyx set out to take matters into his own hands.<br>
<br>
Knowing he was the eldest of the brothers he didn't have a choice of learning patiently the art of arcane magic. He had to hunt for food for him and his young brother. Xanthurok stayed at the wizard guild and began to learn the science. Asphyx was ripping orcs apart so he and his brother could survive. And this kid was making a name for himself quickly.<br>
<br>
